.nh
.TH "BCDOCK" "1" "Jan 2025" "BCDock CLI" "BCDock Manual"

.SH NAME
bcdock-companies-switch - Switch active company context


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBbcdock companies switch  [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
Switch to a different company. All subsequent commands run against the new company.

.PP
New tokens are stored in ~/.bcdock/credentials.json. Pass the company name,
slug, or GUID - the CLI resolves all three.

.PP
Exit codes:
  0   ok
  3   auth failure (missing or invalid token)
  4   rate-limited
  5   company not found


.SH OPTIONS
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for switch


.SH OPTIONS INHERITED FROM PARENT COMMANDS
\fB--api-url\fP=""
	API base URL (env: BCDOCK_API_URL)

.PP
\fB--no-color\fP[=false]
	Disable colored output

.PP
\fB-o\fP, \fB--output\fP="table"
	Output format: table, json, csv

.PP
\fB-q\fP, \fB--quiet\fP[=false]
	Suppress non-essential output

.PP
\fB--timeout\fP=30s
	Request timeout

.PP
\fB--token\fP=""
	API token (env: BCDOCK_TOKEN)


.SH EXAMPLE
.EX
  bcdock companies switch contoso
  bcdock companies switch 3072f5a0-0000-0000-0000-000000000000
.EE


.SH SEE ALSO
\fBbcdock-companies(1)\fP
